---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Callout from '../../components/Callout.astro';

export const title = "Saco Dispensary Guide";
---

<Layout 
  title="Saco Dispensary Guide | Maine Dispensary Guide" 
  description="Complete guide to opening a cannabis dispensary in Saco, Maine. Market analysis, regulations, and investment requirements."
  heroImage="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1500916434205-0c77489c6cf7?auto=format&fit=crop&q=80&w=1200&h=400"
>
  <article>
    <div class="article-header">
      <h1>Saco Dispensary Guide</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">How to open a cannabis dispensary in Saco, Maine</p>
    </div>

    <section>
      <h2>Overview</h2>
      <p>Saco, a charming coastal city in York County with 19,000+ residents, offers a unique opportunity in southern Maine's cannabis market. Located between Portland and the popular beach destinations of Old Orchard Beach and Scarborough, Saco provides access to both local residents and seasonal tourists seeking quality cannabis products. Before moving forward, familiarize yourself with the <a href="/guides/maine-cannabis-real-estate/">real estate requirements</a> essential for success.</p>
    </section>

    <Callout title="Saco: A Local Opportunity" type="passion">
      Operating in Saco is more than just a business; it's about becoming a pillar of the community. Focus on local engagement and education to build lasting trust with your neighbors.
    </Callout>


    <section>
      <h2>Why Saco?</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Coastal Location</strong> - Access to beach tourism market</li>
        <li><strong>Between Portland & Beaches</strong> - Prime strategic position</li>
        <li><strong>Growing Community</strong> - Strong family demographic</li>
        <li><strong>Lower Competition</strong> - Underserved market</li>
        <li><strong>Seasonal Boost</strong> - Summer tourist population</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Saco Market</h2>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Factor</th><th>Assessment</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Population</td><td>19,000+</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Seasonal Visitors</td><td>+30,000+ summer</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Competition</td><td>Low</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Real Estate</td><td>Moderate ($15-22/sq ft)</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Access</td><td>I-95, Route 1</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Local Regulations</h2>
      <p>As part of York County, Saco operates under <a href="https://www.maine.gov/dafs/ocp/rules" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Maine OCP regulations</a>. You'll need to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Obtain state license from Maine Office of Cannabis Policy</li>
        <li>Confirm local zoning allows cannabis businesses</li>
        <li>Meet all state compliance requirements</li>
        <li>Complete employee authorization process</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Best Locations</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Route 1</strong> - Main commercial corridor</li>
        <li><strong>Industrial Park Road</strong> - Commercial zoning</li>
        <li><strong>Near I-95 Exit</strong> - High visibility</li>
        <li><strong>Downtown Saco</strong> - Historic district</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Investment Requirements</h2>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Category</th><th>Estimated Cost</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Real Estate (lease)</td><td>$2,500-4,000/mo</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Build-out</td><td>$90,000-160,000</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Total Investment</td><td>$350,000-600,000</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </section>

    <section class="further-reading">
      <h2>Further Reading</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="https://www.maine.gov/dafs/ocp/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Maine Office of Cannabis Policy (OCP)</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://www.maine.gov/dafs/ocp/rules" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Maine Cannabis Rules</a></li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="disclaimer">
      <p><em>This is for informational purposes only and does not constitute legal or financial advice. Consult with qualified professionals.</em></p>
    </section>
  </article>
</Layout>

<style>
  article { max-width: 720px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .article-header { margin-bottom: 2rem; padding-bottom: 1.5rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
  .subtitle { font-size: 1.25rem; color: var(--color-text-light); }
  section { margin-bottom: 2rem; }
  section h2, section h3 { margin-top: 1.5rem; }
  section h2:first-child { margin-top: 0; }
  table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 1rem 0; }
  th, td { padding: 0.75rem; text-align: left; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
  th { background: var(--color-background); }
  ul { padding-left: 1.5rem; }
  li { margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .disclaimer { background: #fff3cd; border: 1px solid #ffc107; padding: 1rem; border-radius: 0.5rem; font-size: 0.875rem; margin-top: 2rem; }
  .further-reading { background: rgba(88, 129, 87, 0.05); padding: 1.5rem; border-radius: 1rem; margin-top: 3rem; }
  .further-reading h2 { margin-top: 0; font-size: 1.25rem; }
</style>
